GitLab is an open core software company that develops the most comprehensive AI-powered DevSecOps Platform, used
by more than 100,000 organizations. Our mission is to enable everyone to contribute to and co-create the software that
powers our world. When everyone can contribute, consumers become contributors, significantly accelerating the rate of
human progress. This mission is integral to our culture, influencing how we hire, build products, and lead our industry.
We make this possible at GitLab by running our operations on our product and staying aligned with our values. Learn
more about Life at GitLab.
As the Group Manager, Product, you will be responsible for managing and building a team that focuses on GitLab's Plan
stage product categories. This role will lead the Plan Product Managers and reports to the VP of Product.
You will play a key role in defining our product strategy for our Plan stage which includes project management, product
planning, knowledge management, and optimization tools. The focus right now is to mature all Plan categories Find out
more about what it is like to be a PM at GitLab and what the current and future roadmap for Plan looks like here:
Product Manager Handbook page
Product Stage Vision - Plan
What you'll do
Make sure you have a great product team (recruit and hire, sense of progress, promote proactively, identify
underperformance)
Work on the vision with the Product Leadership including VP of Product, Chief Product Officer and CEO; and
communicate this vision internally and externally
Distill the overall vision into a compelling roadmap
Make sure the vision advances in every release and communicate this
Communicate our vision through customer conversations, demos, blogging, and interviews
Work closely with your stable counterparts in R&D including Engineering, UX and Quality along with stakeholders
across Go to Market (Marketing, Sales, etc).
What you'll bring
Experience leading a team of Product Managers
Experience as a Product Manager with recognised achievements during your tenure as an IC
Experience hiring teams in high-growth companies
Experience in DevOps
Experience as a user of a tool like Jira, Monday, Trello
Technical background or clear understanding of work management and planning tools; familiarity with Agile
methodologies, project management, knowledge management, and value stream optimization a plus
You share our values and work in accordance with those values
Additional requirements are outlined in our handbook
About the team
You will be leading a geographically distributed team of Product Managers while working closely with Engineering and
UX counterparts. The team is focused on GitLab's Plan stage, which provides tools for teams to manage and optimize
their work, track operational health, and measure outcomes across project management, product planning, knowledge
management, and optimization capabilities.
